						               													<description>Theme&amp;#10;Players try to win most of the dwarves' treasure.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Goal&amp;#10;Collect as many plastic chips (&amp;quot;gold coins&amp;quot;) as possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game play&amp;#10;The board shows one central circle and 9 circles arranged around it. Each circle has a number from 2 to 11 printed at the center, and a number of small markings corresponding to that number around it. A plastic pot filled with plastic chips is placed on the central circle.&amp;#10;Players take turns rolling the two six-sided dice. The result of a roll is added up and a chip is placed on one of the markings on the corresponding circle (e. g. if you roll a 4 and a 5, you put a chip on one of the markings on circle 9).&amp;#10;If you roll a 12, you put a chip on a circle of your choice.&amp;#10;When all markings on one circle have been filled and that number is rolled again, the player wins the chips from that circle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when a player has collected 20 chips or when there are no chips left in the pot. The player who has collected the most chips wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
